            There will always be difficulties when we attempt to change the entirely erroneous belief of virtually everyone in this country&#x2014; not just in London&#x2014; that someone who owns a car has an absolute right to drive it where and when they like and park it where they like. We must not only improve the environment of London but ensure that its economy is sustainable. Traffic in London costs far too much. It must be properly managed and it must make a decent return to improve public transport.
